Series I: Notebooks

Scope and Contents note

This series contains Frank Moore's art notebooks and sketchpads. Materials are organized in loose chronological order as established by the Gesso Foundation.

Series II: Art Files

Scope and Contents note

This series contains materials relating to Frank Moore's professional career. It is divided into four subseries. The first, subseries A, includes reviews and articles about Frank Moore and his work, announcements for shows, and publications containing his artwork. Subseries B contains administrative files, loan agreements, and financial information. Subseries C consists of notes and lists relating to the day-to-day aspects of his art career. Finally, subseries D includes files of materials Frank Moore collected of other artists' work and careers. Subseries A, B and C are arranged chronologically. Subseries D is arranged alphabetically by the artist's last name.

Series IV: Source Material

Scope and Contents note

This series contains seven subseries; Subseries A: magazines, Subseries B: catalogues, Subseries C: images, Subseries D: articles, Subseries E: photographs, Subseries F: books and Subseries G: ephemera. These materials served as research, inspiration and models for Frank Moore's artwork. Where possible, materials are organized alphabetically by author or title.

Series V: Beehive

Scope and Contents note

Series V includes all materials from the production of Frank Moore and Jim Self's collaborative film "Beehive" as well as the Boston Ballet production. The series is divided into eight subseries containing the film, video and audio production elements, technical notations and lab related paperwork, production materials corresponding to the Beehive film, production materials corresponding to Beehive the ballet, promotional materials, artifacts, as well as film and video preservation elements and access copies. Subseries A Film and subseries B: technical notations and lab related paperwork are organized chronologically by unique object identification number. Subseries C: Production materials Beehive film, D: Production materials Beehive Ballet, E: Promotional materials and F: Artifacts are organized alphabetically. Subseries G: Preservation elements - film and video and H: Access copies - film and video are organized numerically by unique object identification number.
